396
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,800
Oh, you mean uglier.

397
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:53,750
Do you hear that?

398
00:20:54,370 --> 00:20:55,300
Hear what?

399
00:20:55,460 --> 00:20:56,410
I don't hear anything.

400
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,710
Sounds like Doc.

401
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,970
Make it stop!

402
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:12,330
Make it stop!

403
00:21:12,850 --> 00:21:15,420
That's Doc all right. But where the hell is he?

404
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:16,430
Somewhere up there.

405
00:21:16,430 --> 00:21:17,940
We're going up after him.

406
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:19,440
No, you don't.

407
00:21:19,530 --> 00:21:20,520
Let us up now.

408
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:23,820
Nobody goes upstairs without the General's orders.

409
00:21:24,740 --> 00:21:25,860
We go up now

410
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:29,350
or I scramble your egg-brain inside the shell.

411
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:34,720
You'll be sorry.

412
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,920
So will you cuz you're coming up with us.

413
00:21:38,410 --> 00:21:40,480
10K! Cover our flank.

414
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,270
Don't let man or zombie follow us up.

415
00:21:42,270 --> 00:21:43,620
Yes, sir.

416
00:21:48,630 --> 00:21:50,150
One thousand ninety-three.

417
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:52,830
No.

418
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,410
Ninety-four.

419
00:22:02,510 --> 00:22:03,980
What floor is the General on?

420
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,040
Top floor.

421
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:07,080
He's the General, man.

422
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:08,930
What floor do you think he's on?

423
00:22:22,530 --> 00:22:24,140
My world is but an illusion.

424
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,200
My world is but an illusion.

425
00:22:26,260 --> 00:22:28,400
Oh God, why didn't I pay better attention

426
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,610
to that sweet little Buddhist chick I dated?

427
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:34,300
Stay calm.

428
00:22:34,310 --> 00:22:35,260
I'm sure they're...

429
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:36,590
I'm sure they're watching you right now.

430
00:22:36,590 --> 00:22:37,860
They're looking for you.

431
00:22:37,860 --> 00:22:38,850
They're looking for you right now.

432
00:22:38,850 --> 00:22:40,890
There's no way they'd just leave you here

433
00:22:40,890 --> 00:22:43,790
trapped in the air shaft with an ugly-ass zombie

434
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:46,100
waiting to eat my face off!

435
00:22:47,730 --> 00:22:48,870
Oh, wait.

436
00:22:54,170 --> 00:22:55,310
Oh, that's more like it.

437
00:22:55,310 --> 00:22:57,420
I was saving this for a special occasion.

438
00:22:59,180 --> 00:23:00,190
Like now.

439
00:23:08,270 --> 00:23:09,480
Come on, suck it up.

440
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,770
Come on. Come on.

441
00:23:15,490 --> 00:23:17,090
That's good shit, man.

442
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:18,340
Chill!

443
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:23,720
Help!

444
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:28,390
Now what?

445
00:23:29,540 --> 00:23:30,940
Be ready for anything.

446
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:32,600
Did I mention that

447
00:23:32,610 --> 00:23:34,150
the one thing I have a phobia of aside

448
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:37,170
from zombies is elevators.

449
00:23:37,170 --> 00:23:39,110
Shouldn't have messed with the General.

450
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:41,690
Is it getting hot in here?

451
00:23:44,010 --> 00:23:45,800
Hey, come on. Open the damn door.

452
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:46,590
I got to get out of here.

453
00:23:46,590 --> 00:23:47,570
Relax, Murphy.

454
00:23:47,570 --> 00:23:49,030
No, no, I got to get out. There's not enough oxygen.

455
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:52,230
Chill out!

456
00:23:54,970 --> 00:23:55,730
Mack!

457
00:23:55,730 --> 00:23:56,660
I'm here, babe.

458
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,490
Hey, why aren't we moving?

459
00:23:59,490 --> 00:24:01,450
It'll start in a second.

460
00:24:39,590 --> 00:24:40,650
Thank you, son.

461
00:24:42,070 --> 00:24:43,730
It's good.

462
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:45,380
Can I do anything for you?

463
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:48,280
Make sure those knots are tight.

464
00:24:51,250 --> 00:24:52,820
It's not gonna be long now.

465
00:24:54,180 --> 00:24:55,900
It's double-half-hitch. Just like you taught me.

466
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,280
Just be sure.

467
00:25:00,010 --> 00:25:01,170
Promise me

468
00:25:02,340 --> 00:25:04,000
you'll do what we talked about

469
00:25:04,660 --> 00:25:06,070
when the time comes.

470
00:25:09,370 --> 00:25:10,540
Promise me.

471
00:25:12,190 --> 00:25:13,220
I promise.

472
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:15,430
Just like we talked about.

473
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:18,180
I swear.

474
00:25:19,770 --> 00:25:21,020
Don't swear.

475
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,930
Your mother never liked that.

476
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,500
I promise.

477
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:30,480
Good.

478
00:25:32,270 --> 00:25:35,480
I could always trust you to do the right thing.

479
00:25:42,170 --> 00:25:43,540
You're a good boy.

480
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:47,880
Your mother,

481
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:50,980
she'd be proud of the man you're growing up to be.

482
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:58,690
Give me another puff.

483
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,380
Will ya?

484
00:26:28,100 --> 00:26:30,480
Ya know, now don't take offense.

485
00:26:31,390 --> 00:26:35,420
But the only thing worse than that mug of yours

486
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:37,320
is your breath.

487
00:26:41,930 --> 00:26:44,060
Not my fingers, you animal!

488
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,060
I was offering you the last hit.

489
00:26:46,410 --> 00:26:49,130
Well, fine. I'll bogart it myself then.

490
00:26:52,230 --> 00:26:54,820
A thousand and one uses, I tell ya.

491
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:03,770
Well I'll be damned.

492
00:27:04,140 --> 00:27:05,620
I think you're stoned.

493
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:09,400
Hell, we don't need a vaccine.

494
00:27:09,770 --> 00:27:13,230
Just need a few billion tons of some primo Ganja,

495
00:27:13,230 --> 00:27:15,550
and the world would be just fine.

496
00:27:29,970 --> 00:27:31,150
Doctor Morgan Henley.

497
00:27:31,170 --> 00:27:32,910
Does that name ring a bell

498
00:27:33,530 --> 00:27:37,400
