00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:09,080
Me too.

578
00:33:11,570 --> 00:33:13,340
Well look who.

579
00:33:14,890 --> 00:33:16,450
I think that's the last of them.

580
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:20,980
Is everybody okay?

581
00:33:21,460 --> 00:33:22,850
Anybody seen Murphy?

582
00:33:23,500 --> 00:33:25,060
Murphy! Murphy!

583
00:33:25,060 --> 00:33:26,750
You don't have to shout. I'm right here.

584
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:28,300
You don't sneak up on people

585
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:29,430
in the zombie apocalypse, okay?

586
00:33:29,430 --> 00:33:30,600
Sorry, sorry.

587
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:31,550
I know where Doc is.

588
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:32,480
Where?

589
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:51,300
Holy shit.

590
00:34:00,870 --> 00:34:01,660
I'm out of ammo.

591
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:02,760
Me too.

592
00:34:06,430 --> 00:34:07,500
I got this.

593
00:34:37,620 --> 00:34:38,640
Garnett!

594
00:34:44,970 --> 00:34:46,240
Take cover!

595
00:34:51,710 --> 00:34:52,710
No!

596
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:54,320
No!

597
00:34:59,210 --> 00:35:00,300
Is everybody okay?

598
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:01,670
Yeah.

599
00:35:12,740 --> 00:35:14,510
Murphy, where's Doc?

600
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:18,780
He was down that air shaft.

601
00:35:20,060 --> 00:35:21,000
What?

602
00:35:27,180 --> 00:35:28,780
Let's go find that helicopter

603
00:35:28,980 --> 00:35:30,300
and get out of here.

604
00:35:32,040 --> 00:35:33,020
Now.

605
00:35:39,740 --> 00:35:41,260
No disrespect Madame President,

606
00:35:41,260 --> 00:35:43,560
but you're not fit to lead a gang of kindergartners

607
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:44,890
in a dirt clod war.

608
00:35:44,890 --> 00:35:48,200
Let alone this great nation in a moment of grave national peril

609
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:50,120
like we find ourselves in now.

610
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:02,520
I've been waiting for you.

611
00:36:09,250 --> 00:36:10,380
Ah, crap.

612
00:36:10,780 --> 00:36:12,450
Nothing works anymore.

613
00:36:13,780 --> 00:36:14,770
Nothing.

614
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:21,070
What do you people want anyway?

615
00:36:22,060 --> 00:36:24,290
We're on a mission that just might save the human race.

616
00:36:24,290 --> 00:36:26,980
This man has antibodies in his blood

617
00:36:26,980 --> 00:36:28,810
needed to make a zombie vaccine.

618
00:36:28,820 --> 00:36:30,060
We've been tasked with getting him

619
00:36:30,060 --> 00:36:32,540
to a CDC lab in California.

620
00:36:32,540 --> 00:36:33,090
Alive.

621
00:36:33,090 --> 00:36:34,600
We need your helicopter.

622
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,670
Well hell, why didn't you say so sooner?

623
00:36:42,630 --> 00:36:44,370
I'll fly you there myself.

624
00:36:46,530 --> 00:36:47,910
She's beautiful, isn't she?

625
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:49,580
What is this, some kind of joke?

626
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:51,930
Sure, she needs a little maintenance.

627
00:36:51,940 --> 00:36:52,850
But,

628
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:54,820
with some TLC,

629
00:36:55,490 --> 00:36:56,980
a little help scrounging a few spare parts,

630
00:36:56,980 --> 00:36:58,770
I'll have you to California in no time.

631
00:36:58,770 --> 00:36:59,890
Jackass!

632
00:36:59,890 --> 00:37:02,450
A friend of mine died trying to get to that pile of junk.

633
00:37:02,450 --> 00:37:03,730
You and Doc were friends?

634
00:37:03,730 --> 00:37:06,110
We played cards...once.

635
00:37:06,110 --> 00:37:07,920
This is war, son.

636
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:09,660
We've all lost friends.

637
00:37:09,660 --> 00:37:11,290
Hell, everybody I ever knew is dead.

638
00:37:11,300 --> 00:37:12,970
Why am I not surprised?

639
00:37:12,970 --> 00:37:14,130
You know I don't like you.

640
00:37:14,140 --> 00:37:15,170
Well get in line.

641
00:37:15,170 --> 00:37:16,390
General McCandles.

642
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,450
Sir.

643
00:37:18,410 --> 00:37:20,750
Thank you, but I think we'll find alternate transportation.

644
00:37:20,750 --> 00:37:22,740
You think I'm insane, don't you?

645
00:37:27,790 --> 00:37:29,170
Well maybe I am.

646
00:37:31,870 --> 00:37:33,070
Too much death.

647
00:37:34,550 --> 00:37:37,020
Too many good men sent to an early grave.

648
00:37:40,630 --> 00:37:42,080
Too many zombies.

649
00:37:46,010 --> 00:37:47,920
Stand down! I got this!

650
00:37:47,940 --> 00:37:51,220
Come here you Godless brain eating scum!

651
00:37:54,180 --> 00:37:56,570
I'll see you in Hell!

652
00:38:09,690 --> 00:38:11,020
What happened to Doc?

653
00:38:15,770 --> 00:38:16,890
He didn't make it.

654
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:25,730
Zombies.

655
00:38:29,850 --> 00:38:31,310
Oh God, is that...

656
00:38:32,490 --> 00:38:33,500
It's Doc.

657
00:38:40,790 --> 00:38:41,940
Someone's gotta...

658
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:43,060
I'll do it.

659
00:38:45,970 --> 00:38:48,580
Steven "Doc" Beck.

660
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:54,160
I give you mercy.

661
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:01,940
What the hell, Warren?

662
00:39:01,940 --> 00:39:03,510
You trying to kill me?

663
00:39:05,070 --> 00:39:06,160
You're alive?

664
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:08,030
Damn straight I'm alive.

665
00:39:11,810 --> 00:39:13,170
We thought you were dead.

666
00:39:13,170 --> 00:39:14,770
Well so did I.

667
00:39:15,010 --> 00:39:17,400
Some numbskull threw a grenade

668
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:19,810
in the air shaft I was stuck in.

669
00:39:22,390 --> 00:39:23,290
Well hurry up!

670
00:39:23,300 --> 00:39:23,850
Here.

671
00:39:23,850 --> 00:39:24,890
Come on.

672
00:39:25,100 --> 00:39:26,720
Give me a kiss, baby.

673
00:39:36,250 --> 00:39:38,190
Well I should let you go.

674
00:39:38,450 --> 00:39:39,740
I'm sure you're busy with

675
00:39:39,740 --> 00:39:41,620
keeping an eye on the world and all.

676
00:39:43,980 --> 00:39:44,860
Yeah.

677
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:47,680
I got a hungry dog here I better go feed.

678
00:39:48,410 --> 00:39:49,750
Nice talking to you.

679
00:39:50,430 --> 00:39:52,060
I hope we get to meet someday.

680
00:39:54,690 --> 00:39:56,220
I'd really like that.

681
00:39:56,710 --> 00:39:57,660
Good night.

682
00:39:59,590 --> 00:40:01,080
Sweet prince.

684
00:40:03,420 --> 00:40:05,990
Good night, fair lady.

685
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:21,310
Here's a song for all the lonely people out there,

686
00:40:21,380 --> 00:40:23,600
which is just about everybody that's left.

687
00:40:24,420 --> 00:40:26,830
So if you've got somebody to go through the Apocalypse with,

688
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:29,390
you better watch their backs.

689
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:31,580
Cuz there ain't many of us left.

690
00:40:32,790 --> 00:40:33,860
And oh yeah,

692
00:40:35,010 --> 00:40:37,810
I'd like to dedicate this song to Addison Carver,

693
00:40:39,060 --> 00:40:40,190
wherever you are.

694
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:44,870
I'd like to dedicate this song to Addison Carver,

695
00:40:45,380 --> 00:40:46,430
wherever you are.

696
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:51,070
I talked to the guy twice. Come on.

697
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:57,520
You know kid,

698
00:40:58,610 --> 00:41:01,380
I've been thinking about what you told me about your dad

699
00:41:02,100 --> 00:41:04,750
and how you wished he knew you did the right thing

700
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:07,040
giving him mercy like you promised.

701
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:08,240
Yeah?

702
00:41:09,510 --> 00:41:11,340
Well I just want you to know

703
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:14,580
your dad knows what you did for him.

704
00:41:14,810 --> 00:41:16,560
And he knows you did the right thing.

705
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:17,990
You kept your promise.

706
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:22,630
Thanks.

707
00:41:45,490 --> 00:41:46,840
I'm sorry, papa.

708
00:41:53,530 --> 00:41:54,470
I love you.

